Samsung Electronics May Invest $94 Million in Phone Carrier, Chosun Says

-- B y   S h i n h y e   K a n g
-- 
2011-07-10T23:42:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/samsung-electronics-may-invest-94-million-in-phone-carrier-chosun-says.html
Samsung Electronics Co. may invest
about 100 billion won in a new mobile-phone operator to be set
up by former South Korean communications minister Yang Seung
Taek and Korea Federation of Small and Medium Business, the
Chosun Ilbo newspaper reported. The new company may offer
consumers cheaper services, the Korean-language newspaper said,
citing Yang.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shinhye Kang at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net  